WEBVTT

1
00:03:42.129 --> 00:03:43.464
You should've quit after Godfried.

2
00:03:47.718 --> 00:03:49.220
Stop it now. Come on, guys.

3
00:04:52.199 --> 00:04:53.534
Was it a busy night?

4
00:04:54.869 --> 00:04:55.911
It was OK.

5
00:04:55.995 --> 00:04:58.414
You must be glad
you can finally go to bed.


6
00:05:01.041 --> 00:05:02.334
I quite like blondes.

7
00:05:03.252 --> 00:05:05.087
Or brunettes. I don't care.

8
00:05:08.799 --> 00:05:11.218
Someone like you is worth her price.

9
00:05:15.598 --> 00:05:16.807
What do you think you're doing?

10
00:05:16.891 --> 00:05:17.933
Sure you have money on you?

11
00:05:18.058 --> 00:05:19.643
Of course I do!

12
00:05:19.769 --> 00:05:21.437
This ride is free, darling...

13
00:05:21.562 --> 00:05:23.147
if you'd be so kind?

14
00:05:25.524 --> 00:05:27.109
I've finished for tonight, darling.

15
00:05:27.193 --> 00:05:29.445
Don't be such a baby.
Put in some overtime.


16
00:05:32.364 --> 00:05:33.908
Just take me home.

17
00:05:36.160 --> 00:05:37.328
Shut up!

18
00:05:37.453 --> 00:05:39.079
Fucking bitch! 
Who do you think you are?

19
00:05:39.205 --> 00:05:41.332
Don't take me for a mug.

20
00:05:42.166 --> 00:05:43.501
Dirty slut.

21
00:05:43.584 --> 00:05:44.919
Get on with it.

22
00:05:53.093 --> 00:05:54.178
Fucking whore.

23
00:06:20.913 --> 00:06:22.665
Are you all right, girl?

24
00:06:22.790 --> 00:06:24.792
Yes, I'm OK.

25
00:08:08.687 --> 00:08:10.397
Welcome to Amsterdam.

26
00:08:10.481 --> 00:08:12.066
The capital of Holland,

27
00:08:12.149 --> 00:08:15.653
and world famous for its many canals.

28
00:08:16.028 --> 00:08:19.156
There are over 165 canals,

29
00:08:19.281 --> 00:08:22.326
totaling a length of ten miles.

30
00:08:22.451 --> 00:08:24.328
They run through the whole city,

31
00:08:24.453 --> 00:08:28.415
and were dug in the 17th century
to transport goods from the harbor


32
00:08:28.540 --> 00:08:30.709
to the merchants' warehouses.

33
00:08:30.793 --> 00:08:33.837
Amsterdam has 750,000 residents,

34
00:08:33.921 --> 00:08:37.383
who all live in
approximately 200,000 houses.


35
00:08:37.466 --> 00:08:40.177
These are all built on wooden piles.

36
00:08:40.260 --> 00:08:43.263
Amsterdam was built
on about 100,000 wooden piles.


37
00:08:43.347 --> 00:08:46.183
So don't stamp too hard,
or the whole city will collapse.


38
00:10:03.886 --> 00:10:05.429
Be careful, it's loaded.

39
00:10:05.554 --> 00:10:07.806
Your final hour has come.

40
00:10:07.931 --> 00:10:10.517
Put it back. It's not a toy.

41
00:10:15.022 --> 00:10:16.607
You forgot the bullets.

42
00:10:17.900 --> 00:10:19.985
You've been in the
bath for half an hour!

43
00:10:20.110 --> 00:10:22.196
And yesterday you came home far too late.

44
00:10:22.321 --> 00:10:24.406
Is that a reason to shoot your dad?

45
00:10:24.490 --> 00:10:26.325
It's nearly 8:45 a.m.

46
00:10:27.159 --> 00:10:29.411
You'll make me late for school.

47
00:10:29.495 --> 00:10:31.330
You don't have to wait for me.

48
00:10:31.413 --> 00:10:33.248
You said you'd take me, remember?

49
00:10:33.373 --> 00:10:35.084
My bicycle was stolen yesterday.

50
00:10:35.209 --> 00:10:36.585
Oh yes, I forgot.

51
00:10:36.710 --> 00:10:39.004
Why don't you people
do something about that?


52
00:10:39.088 --> 00:10:42.925
Do you know how many bicycles
are stolen in Amsterdam every year?


53
00:10:43.258 --> 00:10:46.386
I haven't the foggiest. Two? Three?

54
00:10:47.763 --> 00:10:49.556
Hello. Anneke Visser speaking.

55
00:10:50.265 --> 00:10:53.227
He's been playing with himself
in the bath for the last half hour.


56
00:10:53.894 --> 00:10:56.980
Yes. Eric! Police Headquarters for you.

57
00:11:04.780 --> 00:11:05.948
Eric speaking.

58
00:11:10.494 --> 00:11:12.621
I do try to
give her a decent upbringing.

59
00:11:14.164 --> 00:11:15.707
I'd said I'd come in later today.

60
00:11:17.793 --> 00:11:19.044
From a bridge?

61
00:11:20.754 --> 00:11:22.589
All right. I'm coming.

62
00:11:24.299 --> 00:11:26.802
- Did they find my bicycle?
- Not yet.


63
00:11:26.885 --> 00:11:28.053
I thought as much.

64
00:11:29.471 --> 00:11:30.848
- Ready?
- Ages ago.


65
00:11:30.973 --> 00:11:33.892
- Have you got all your books?
- Yes! You just get a move on.


66
00:11:33.976 --> 00:11:35.561
Did you feed the cat?

67
00:11:37.104 --> 00:11:38.730
Morning, Amsterdam!

68
00:11:47.030 --> 00:11:48.031
Bye!

69
00:12:02.504 --> 00:12:05.257
FM, 94.3.

70
00:12:05.340 --> 00:12:07.301
City Radio Amsterdam.

71
00:13:16.245 --> 00:13:18.330
The police are on their way.
I've called them.


72
00:13:18.622 --> 00:13:19.665
What about my cake?

73
00:13:20.123 --> 00:13:22.793
Who's paying for that?
You'd think it was for free.


74
00:13:22.918 --> 00:13:24.836
Couldn't you have been more careful?

75
00:13:34.263 --> 00:13:35.555
Give them back to me, OK?

76
00:13:38.058 --> 00:13:40.477
I don't have all day. Twat!

77
00:14:09.423 --> 00:14:10.424
We started without you.

78
00:14:10.507 --> 00:14:11.842
I had to drop by the baker's.

79
00:14:12.467 --> 00:14:13.635
Is that her?

80
00:14:13.760 --> 00:14:15.804
Yes. Badly mutilated with a knife.

81
00:14:15.887 --> 00:14:17.431
The perpetrator must be deranged.

82
00:14:17.472 --> 00:14:18.473
Who is she?

83
00:14:18.598 --> 00:14:20.434
A hooker. Potter is investigating.

84
00:14:20.642 --> 00:14:22.686
They've taken photos. 
The autopsy is next.

85
00:14:22.811 --> 00:14:24.730
- Has she been raped?
- Didn't look like it.


86
00:14:24.813 --> 00:14:28.191
She was stabbed down the street
and dragged into the canal.


87
00:14:28.275 --> 00:14:29.401
This is where she was hanging?

88
00:14:29.860 --> 00:14:32.237
Upside down,
her feet tied with a bowline knot.


89
00:14:32.571 --> 00:14:35.157
- Sailor?
- It's possible.


90
00:14:35.240 --> 00:14:37.075
Good.

91
00:14:37.159 --> 00:14:38.535
Any witnesses?

92
00:14:38.660 --> 00:14:39.953
No, nobody.

93
00:14:40.037 --> 00:14:42.664
No witnesses, no fingerprints.

94
00:14:43.206 --> 00:14:46.043
It must have happened
between 1:00 and 3:00 a.m.


95
00:14:46.126 --> 00:14:48.003
They're dragging the canal.
We may find something.


96
00:14:48.086 --> 00:14:51.673
One has to have a weird sense of humor
to expose your victim like that.


97
00:14:52.341 --> 00:14:53.884
It seems as if he's proud of it.

98
00:14:53.967 --> 00:14:56.178
Hi, Eric. We have a witness.

99
00:14:56.303 --> 00:14:57.763
Are you sure?

100
00:14:57.846 --> 00:15:00.599
Tell this gentleman
what you've told me, please.


101
00:15:02.684 --> 00:15:04.061
It was a monster.

102
00:15:04.144 --> 00:15:05.270
A monster?

103
00:15:05.937 --> 00:15:07.022
I saw it all.

104
00:15:07.397 --> 00:15:09.066
A big, black monster.

105
00:15:09.775 --> 00:15:12.194
With huge claws and feet.

106
00:15:12.778 --> 00:15:13.987
It emerged from the water.

107
00:15:14.071 --> 00:15:16.740
From the water? 
Did he have a boat?

108
00:15:17.324 --> 00:15:20.786
From the water. 
I saw it with my own eyes.

109
00:15:22.913 --> 00:15:24.122
What do you think?

110
00:15:24.206 --> 00:15:27.334
I don't know.
She's not exactly a reliable witness.


111
00:15:27.417 --> 00:15:29.753
But she's the only one we've got
at the moment.


112
00:15:30.003 --> 00:15:32.964
What do you think she means by
"a big, black monster


113
00:15:33.048 --> 00:15:34.341
with huge claws"?

114
00:15:34.800 --> 00:15:36.885
No idea. Does your mother-in-law
have an alibi?


115
00:15:37.969 --> 00:15:40.764
Let's wait for the autopsy.
We can't do much until then.


116
00:15:41.932 --> 00:15:45.143
Maybe the neighborhood search will provide
some clues. I've deployed eight men.


117
00:15:45.268 --> 00:15:48.730
Let's hope so. As yet, it's not a case
that would get you promoted.


118
00:16:02.411 --> 00:16:04.204
Why are you sitting in the dark?

119
00:16:04.704 --> 00:16:05.914
Willy is in a trance.

120
00:16:06.039 --> 00:16:08.834
He says he's able to contact
his deceased aunt.


121
00:16:08.917 --> 00:16:10.627
Oh, here we go again!

122
00:16:11.336 --> 00:16:13.463
I thought he was going to help you
with your homework.


123
00:16:13.547 --> 00:16:15.173
We've finished!

124
00:16:15.799 --> 00:16:18.176
- I can't do it like this.
- Did you make contact?


125
00:16:18.260 --> 00:16:21.096
Almost, but this is not
the right environment.


126
00:16:21.179 --> 00:16:23.014
Whatever.

127
00:16:23.640 --> 00:16:27.018
It requires deep concentration.

128
00:16:27.102 --> 00:16:29.187
I'm going to try again at home.

129
00:16:29.271 --> 00:16:31.898
I think you suck, man.

130
00:16:32.023 --> 00:16:33.191
Can we put the light back on?

131
00:16:33.275 --> 00:16:36.194
Sure, Willy can't concentrate anyway.

132
00:16:36.319 --> 00:16:38.321
You're just jealous
you don't have my gift.


133
00:16:39.114 --> 00:16:40.073
Gift!

134
00:16:40.157 --> 00:16:43.160
- You're not staying for dinner?
- My mother has made macaroni.


135
00:16:43.243 --> 00:16:45.245
- Bye, Mr. Visser.
- Bye, Willy.


136
00:16:45.328 --> 00:16:47.372
- Give my regards to your aunt.
- Will do.


137
00:16:47.456 --> 00:16:48.540
See you tomorrow, Anneke.

138
00:16:48.874 --> 00:16:49.916
Bye-bye.

139
00:16:52.127 --> 00:16:53.253
How was school?

140
00:16:53.336 --> 00:16:54.546
It was OK.

141
00:16:54.629 --> 00:16:56.298
Did you buy any peanut butter?

142
00:16:56.423 --> 00:16:59.259
- Is it gone?
- You forgot to get it yesterday, too.


143
00:16:59.342 --> 00:17:01.636
Then you do the groceries from now on.

144
00:17:01.720 --> 00:17:03.472
And no chocolate sprinkles either.

145
00:17:03.555 --> 00:17:07.309
Honey, there is more to life
than peanut butter and sprinkles.


146
00:17:07.392 --> 00:17:09.519
Yes. Apple spread.

147
00:17:09.603 --> 00:17:12.772
- You didn't get that either.
- Go and set the table.


148
00:17:12.856 --> 00:17:13.857
What are we having?

149
00:17:13.982 --> 00:17:15.525
Brussels sprouts in chocolate sauce.

150
00:17:15.650 --> 00:17:17.110
I don't like Belgian.

151
00:17:18.612 --> 00:17:24.701
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine.


152
00:17:25.285 --> 00:17:26.578
2.25 meters.

153
00:17:26.703 --> 00:17:29.206
3:15 a.m.

154
00:17:29.331 --> 00:17:32.959
2.25 meters.

155
00:17:55.607 --> 00:17:57.442
I think we're wasting our time.

156
00:17:57.901 --> 00:18:00.028
Are you sure this is the right spot?

157
00:18:00.570 --> 00:18:02.864
We're exactly above the pipe.

158
00:18:02.989 --> 00:18:04.658
But we aren't having much luck.

159
00:18:04.741 --> 00:18:06.868
We've only got clear water so far.

160
00:18:07.577 --> 00:18:09.371
Maybe we're above the sewers.

161
00:18:10.038 --> 00:18:12.040
We'll be hauling up buckets of shit next.

162
00:18:12.123 --> 00:18:13.750
Keep your voice down.

163
00:18:13.833 --> 00:18:15.001
They might hear us.

164
00:18:15.085 --> 00:18:17.170
I think that factory
is completely shut down.


165
00:18:17.379 --> 00:18:18.463
We'll be waiting for ages.

166
00:18:18.755 --> 00:18:21.883
I suspect it'll happen any time now.

167
00:18:22.008 --> 00:18:24.135
One lot of waste dumping
is enough to make them hang.


168
00:18:26.304 --> 00:18:28.848
I'll do my own dumping.

169
00:18:32.811 --> 00:18:35.188
What are you waiting for? Hurry up!

170
00:18:37.065 --> 00:18:38.441
The bastards.

171
00:18:38.858 --> 00:18:40.110
We've got them.

172
00:18:40.735 --> 00:18:44.948
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine.


173
00:18:45.282 --> 00:18:46.616
Haul it up.

174
00:18:47.367 --> 00:18:49.452
- Hurry.
- It's stuck.


175
00:18:49.536 --> 00:18:50.662
What do you mean?

176
00:18:54.624 --> 00:18:56.001
What could it be?

177
00:18:56.418 --> 00:18:57.711
Heavy poison.

178
00:19:04.634 --> 00:19:06.136
What the heck!

179
00:19:07.012 --> 00:19:08.513
I want to get out of here, Kees.

180
00:19:14.561 --> 00:19:16.563
Let's go.
There's something fishy going on.


181
00:19:17.314 --> 00:19:18.607
Raise the anchor!

182
00:19:23.653 --> 00:19:26.906
Did you fill it up with petrol
like I asked you to? Hendrik!


183
00:20:47.445 --> 00:20:49.531
- Why are you stopping?
- There was a man on the ground.


184
00:20:49.614 --> 00:20:52.075
- Where?
- On the waterfront.


185
00:20:52.158 --> 00:20:54.202
- I didn't see a thing.
- I did.


186
00:21:17.058 --> 00:21:19.519
Well, did you have a good chat?

187
00:21:20.854 --> 00:21:22.021
He's gone.

188
00:21:22.564 --> 00:21:25.358
It's all this weird stuff
we have to transport all the time.


189
00:21:25.483 --> 00:21:27.777
They make you see things.

190
00:21:28.153 --> 00:21:30.196
I really did see someone.

191
00:21:36.995 --> 00:21:38.955
The morning shift people found the boat.

192
00:21:39.038 --> 00:21:40.540
Nobody from the factory saw anything?

193
00:21:40.665 --> 00:21:42.667
It was shut down due to maintenance work.

194
00:21:42.751 --> 00:21:45.462
There were only two night watchmen
who claim not to have seen anything.


195
00:22:02.228 --> 00:22:03.813
What were they doing last night?

196
00:22:03.897 --> 00:22:06.483
Taking water samples.

197
00:22:06.608 --> 00:22:08.777
It looks like they've been sampled
by the water monster.


198
00:22:08.902 --> 00:22:10.945
You think it's the same one?

199
00:22:11.070 --> 00:22:14.073
The same killer?
I'll let the experts decide.


200
00:22:14.157 --> 00:22:17.994
It would be a mighty coincidence
if there are two such lunatics around.


201
00:22:18.536 --> 00:22:20.205
I've warned you, pal.

202
00:22:20.288 --> 00:22:21.539
If you don't listen...

203
00:22:21.998 --> 00:22:23.208
you'll get hurt.
- There you go.


204
00:22:24.834 --> 00:22:27.629
Who do you think you are? Asshole!

205
00:22:28.963 --> 00:22:30.215
Keep your hair on!

206
00:22:30.298 --> 00:22:33.510
If you take one more pic, I'll shove
that telephoto lens down your throat.


207
00:22:33.593 --> 00:22:36.095
Well, well! No half measures then.

208
00:22:37.972 --> 00:22:39.557
I don't like being photographed.

209
00:22:43.895 --> 00:22:46.648
- It's been a long time.
- Thirteen years, I believe.


210
00:22:46.731 --> 00:22:49.317
Eric, this is John van Meegeren
from the river police.


211
00:22:49.400 --> 00:22:50.693
We have met.

212
00:22:50.985 --> 00:22:53.112
You're going to assist us, 
I've been told.

213
00:22:53.238 --> 00:22:54.989
They thought I might be of help,

214
00:22:55.073 --> 00:22:57.283
with all those bodies
you have to fish out of the water.


215
00:22:57.367 --> 00:22:59.953
Vermeer! Could you come here a second?

216
00:23:01.412 --> 00:23:03.957
- You haven't changed a bit.
- You think?


217
00:23:04.207 --> 00:23:06.292
Still the handsomest one of us both.

218
00:23:06.417 --> 00:23:07.544
Are you still mad at me?

219
00:23:08.127 --> 00:23:10.171
It's no fun when someone
runs off with your girlfriend.


220
00:23:10.588 --> 00:23:11.798
I know all about that.

221
00:23:12.006 --> 00:23:13.883
I hear she's abandoned you, too.

222
00:23:13.967 --> 00:23:15.844
She left me three years ago,

223
00:23:15.927 --> 00:23:17.262
for a painter.

224
00:23:17.387 --> 00:23:19.973
She lives in France now.
She pops over once in a while.


225
00:23:20.139 --> 00:23:21.349
To see Anneke.

226
00:23:21.432 --> 00:23:23.434
You've saved me a lot of grief.

227
00:23:23.893 --> 00:23:25.478
But don't ever do it again.

228
00:23:25.937 --> 00:23:27.313
Whatever you say.

229
00:23:28.314 --> 00:23:29.941
Are you any the wiser?

230
00:23:30.483 --> 00:23:31.693
Not yet.

231
00:23:32.277 --> 00:23:33.528
We're searching the bottom.

232
00:23:33.653 --> 00:23:36.531
It's tricky as the water is very dirty.
Visibility is poor.


233
00:23:38.950 --> 00:23:39.993
He's found something.

234
00:23:48.084 --> 00:23:50.670
- What is it?
- A depth gauge.


235
00:23:50.795 --> 00:23:52.714
Part of a diver's equipment.

236
00:23:52.839 --> 00:23:54.549
We're dealing with a diver?

237
00:23:54.632 --> 00:23:56.217
Who knows how long
it's been in the water?

238
00:23:56.426 --> 00:23:58.428
It needs to be checked.
Take it to the lab.


239
00:23:58.595 --> 00:24:01.139
I want to know how long it's lain
at the bottom and where it's from.


240
00:24:02.640 --> 00:24:06.019
A diver prowling the canals of Amsterdam.

241
00:24:06.561 --> 00:24:09.105
It's not great for our reputation.

242
00:24:09.188 --> 00:24:11.065
It could be a
lot of fun this summer.

243
00:24:11.733 --> 00:24:13.192
A diver?

244
00:24:14.277 --> 00:24:15.486
Isn't that a little far-fetched?

245
00:24:15.695 --> 00:24:20.325
It's currently our best bet,
if we rule out the Loch Ness monster.


246
00:24:20.408 --> 00:24:21.784
But you have no witnesses.

247
00:24:21.868 --> 00:24:24.537
- Nobody has seen or heard anything.
- Exactly.


248
00:24:24.621 --> 00:24:26.706
The canals are a perfect hiding place.

249
00:24:26.831 --> 00:24:29.083
You can move around the whole city
without being noticed.


250
00:24:29.417 --> 00:24:30.585
What are your thoughts, John?

251
00:24:30.752 --> 00:24:33.463
Those two
were completely taken by surprise.


252
00:24:33.713 --> 00:24:36.925
It's unlikely that the killer
sailed up to them in a boat.


253
00:24:37.050 --> 00:24:39.218
Some people have bizarre hobbies.

254
00:24:39.385 --> 00:24:40.762
Do you have enough manpower?

255
00:24:40.845 --> 00:24:42.013
For now.

256
00:24:42.221 --> 00:24:45.308
Keep me posted.
Give me a shout if you need anything.


257
00:24:45.642 --> 00:24:47.852
I hope you won't be needing
any more of those flags.


258
00:24:49.604 --> 00:24:52.398
These are all the registered divers
in Holland.


259
00:24:52.440 --> 00:24:53.441
Great.

260
00:24:53.566 --> 00:24:55.568
Eight and a half thousand suspects.

261
00:24:55.652 --> 00:24:56.986
You're probably among them.

262
00:24:57.153 --> 00:24:58.321
I have an alibi.

263
00:24:58.446 --> 00:25:01.324
I also tracked down the taxi driver.

264
00:25:01.449 --> 00:25:02.742
What did he have to say?

265
00:25:02.825 --> 00:25:05.870
He picked up the victim around 1:30 a.m.

266
00:25:05.954 --> 00:25:10.583
He claims she'd made advances to him
in the car, which he rejected.


267
00:25:10.792 --> 00:25:11.793
He says he chucked her out.

268
00:25:11.918 --> 00:25:13.127
It's likely the other way round.

269
00:25:13.252 --> 00:25:15.546
He's got a watertight alibi
for the rest of the night.


270
00:25:15.672 --> 00:25:16.965
That was to be expected.

271
00:25:23.388 --> 00:25:24.597
Great, let's hear it.

272
00:25:29.268 --> 00:25:30.561
OK, thanks.

273
00:25:31.604 --> 00:25:34.899
They found a small piece of black rubber
on one of the anchor tips.


274
00:25:35.024 --> 00:25:37.068
The lab confirms it's from a wet suit.

275
00:25:37.193 --> 00:25:38.361
We are on the right track.

276
00:25:38.736 --> 00:25:40.738
- Is Potter still investigating that rope?
- Which rope?


277
00:25:40.989 --> 00:25:43.032
The one that was used
to tie our friend to the bridge.


278
00:25:43.116 --> 00:25:44.575
We know the maker.

279
00:25:44.701 --> 00:25:47.036
All the shops and outlets
are being checked.


280
00:25:47.161 --> 00:25:49.956
Good to hear lots of people
are busy making a living.


281
00:25:50.623 --> 00:25:52.750
- It's nearly noon.
- Time for lunch?


282
00:25:52.959 --> 00:25:54.335
If you can stomach it.

283
00:25:56.212 --> 00:25:59.382
Sixteen stab wounds,
at least eight fatal ones.


284
00:26:00.174 --> 00:26:04.470
It was such a mess in there,
some organs have almost swapped places.


285
00:26:05.096 --> 00:26:07.765
A broken neck, two broken ribs.

286
00:26:07.849 --> 00:26:09.934
Shattered nasal bone. 
Water in the lungs.

287
00:26:10.268 --> 00:26:12.186
Several bruises and grazes.

288
00:26:12.270 --> 00:26:14.272
He must have gone berserk.

289
00:26:14.355 --> 00:26:17.358
- And the murder weapon?
- A sharp knife.


290
00:26:18.818 --> 00:26:21.112
Look. This is the tip.

291
00:26:21.863 --> 00:26:24.115
The force of the stabbing
caused it to break off.


292
00:26:24.323 --> 00:26:27.201
It was probably a carving knife,
with a blade measuring


293
00:26:27.493 --> 00:26:29.537
9 to 12 inches.

294
00:26:30.204 --> 00:26:32.540
The stomach contained some red wine

295
00:26:32.665 --> 00:26:34.042
and the remains of two hamburgers,

296
00:26:34.375 --> 00:26:36.085
most likely from McDonald's.

297
00:26:36.377 --> 00:26:38.588
Was she dead before she hit the water?

298
00:26:38.755 --> 00:26:40.048
Not quite.

299
00:26:40.298 --> 00:26:42.467
That explains
the amount of water in the lungs.


300
00:26:42.925 --> 00:26:44.719
The job was finished under water.

301
00:26:45.511 --> 00:26:49.140
But she was dead before
she was suspended from the bridge.


302
00:26:50.475 --> 00:26:52.602
This one can go back in the freezer.

303
00:26:53.352 --> 00:26:55.313
And here we have our fishing friends.

304
00:26:56.147 --> 00:26:58.733
They were savaged even more viciously.

305
00:26:59.275 --> 00:27:02.320
I'll save you the irrelevant details.

306
00:27:03.196 --> 00:27:05.198
One of them was decapitated.

307
00:27:05.823 --> 00:27:08.367
Everything seems to indicate
that it happened under water.


308
00:27:08.826 --> 00:27:11.829
Both stomachs showed
remains of a vegetarian meal.


309
00:27:12.371 --> 00:27:14.874
Lentils, millet, carrot juice...

310
00:27:14.957 --> 00:27:17.293
But one of them had eaten
a sausage afterwards.


311
00:27:17.627 --> 00:27:19.337
A knife was used here as well.

312
00:27:19.796 --> 00:27:21.297
But a different type.

313
00:27:21.547 --> 00:27:24.092
This one had a serrated blade.

314
00:27:24.759 --> 00:27:26.677
I've seen it once before.

315
00:27:26.886 --> 00:27:28.429
- It concerned...
- A dive knife.


316
00:27:28.679 --> 00:27:30.932
- That's right.
- A dive knife?


317
00:27:31.307 --> 00:27:33.559
Every diver has a knife on him.

318
00:27:33.935 --> 00:27:37.438
So they can cut themselves loose
in case they get stuck somewhere.


319
00:27:37.563 --> 00:27:40.483
In this case, it was used
for a very different purpose.


320
00:27:45.530 --> 00:27:47.073
Now we know who we're looking for,

321
00:27:47.198 --> 00:27:48.866
how are we going to catch the bastard?

322
00:27:48.950 --> 00:27:51.285
You tell me.
After all, it's one of your colleagues.


323
00:27:51.494 --> 00:27:53.412
The only thing I know about him

324
00:27:53.496 --> 00:27:56.165
is that he is strong,
has a black wet suit,


325
00:27:56.290 --> 00:27:57.750
and probably misses his depth gauge.

326
00:27:57.834 --> 00:27:59.752
Not enough to arrest someone.

327
00:27:59.836 --> 00:28:01.712
No, it doesn't get us anywhere.

328
00:28:01.796 --> 00:28:03.381
Apart from the registered divers,

329
00:28:03.506 --> 00:28:06.384
there are at least 10,000 sport divers
in Holland.


330
00:28:06.592 --> 00:28:09.053
Let's start our search around Amsterdam.

331
00:28:09.303 --> 00:28:11.973
It has to be someone
who knows the city and its canals well.


332
00:28:12.557 --> 00:28:13.891
A top-off, gentlemen?

333
00:28:13.975 --> 00:28:15.143
Yes, please.

334
00:28:19.147 --> 00:28:22.650
That murdered quiz master three years ago.

335
00:28:22.775 --> 00:28:25.236
- You didn't have many clues then either.
- Did you follow that case?


336
00:28:25.319 --> 00:28:27.613
- It was in all the newspapers.
- We had zilch.


337
00:28:27.738 --> 00:28:31.159
At first we suspected the candidates
who'd never won anything.


338
00:28:31.242 --> 00:28:33.411
But everyone had a watertight alibi.

339
00:28:34.954 --> 00:28:37.165
It took us nine weeks
to find the perpetrator.


340
00:28:37.415 --> 00:28:39.292
How did you track him down?

341
00:28:39.625 --> 00:28:42.253
Sometimes you need patience,
some intuition,


342
00:28:42.420 --> 00:28:45.631
and luck. A little luck goes a long way
in our profession.


343
00:28:58.019 --> 00:28:59.061
SEA WOLF

344
00:29:29.842 --> 00:29:31.177
Can I help you?

345
00:29:31.552 --> 00:29:34.305
- I'm just looking around.
- You don't want to become a member?


346
00:29:34.388 --> 00:29:36.515
- No, I'm a detective.
- I knew it.


347
00:29:37.058 --> 00:29:39.352
You people have gone over
the records this morning.


348
00:29:39.435 --> 00:29:41.395
These things are unavoidable, sir.

349
00:29:41.479 --> 00:29:43.272
What do you do here?

350
00:29:43.356 --> 00:29:44.815
I'm the manager here.

351
00:29:44.899 --> 00:29:46.651
I already told you people this morning.

352
00:29:46.734 --> 00:29:48.069
What are you doing here?

353
00:29:48.194 --> 00:29:50.404
This is the largest diving society
in Amsterdam.


354
00:29:50.488 --> 00:29:52.490
In The Netherlands. 
And the best one.

355
00:29:52.573 --> 00:29:55.076
Don't think we only bother you.

356
00:29:55.785 --> 00:29:57.703
Do you mind if
I have a look around?

357
00:29:58.079 --> 00:29:59.956
I am not in
a position to refuse you.

358
00:30:01.332 --> 00:30:03.125
This is where our gear is stored.

359
00:30:03.251 --> 00:30:05.211
Our members are allowed to use it freely.

360
00:30:05.378 --> 00:30:08.172
- How many members are there?
- Over 1,400.


361
00:30:14.720 --> 00:30:16.264
Do you lose many of these?

362
00:30:16.347 --> 00:30:17.598
How do you mean?

363
00:30:17.765 --> 00:30:20.309
Do the members return everything
you lend them?


364
00:30:20.393 --> 00:30:22.228
I've never had any problems.

365
00:30:22.353 --> 00:30:25.481
You don't suppose one of our members
is involved with those murders?


366
00:30:25.731 --> 00:30:27.525
We all do weird things at times.

367
00:30:27.650 --> 00:30:29.360
All our members are respectable people.

368
00:30:29.443 --> 00:30:32.154
They have better things to do
than swim in those filthy canals.


369
00:30:32.905 --> 00:30:34.323
You can't see a thing in there.

370
00:30:34.490 --> 00:30:37.326
And the rubbish they dump
gives you all kinds of diseases.


371
00:30:37.451 --> 00:30:38.536
No.

372
00:30:38.619 --> 00:30:41.580
We organize trips to the sea, or abroad.

373
00:30:41.706 --> 00:30:43.124
We look for derelicts,

374
00:30:43.249 --> 00:30:45.126
or coral reefs. 
It's a proper sport.

375
00:30:46.377 --> 00:30:49.422
I can't imagine anyone
diving in those canals for fun.


376
00:30:49.547 --> 00:30:52.550
You've got a whole weapon arsenal.

377
00:30:52.633 --> 00:30:54.343
We have all the permits.

378
00:30:54.677 --> 00:30:57.888
All divers are required to have one.
Careful, it's sharp.


379
00:30:58.931 --> 00:31:00.266
I know.

380
00:31:01.684 --> 00:31:04.979
And this? Is that also a requirement?

381
00:31:05.187 --> 00:31:06.856
It's for angling.

382
00:31:08.232 --> 00:31:09.275
For sharks?

383
00:31:09.900 --> 00:31:11.152
If they become too curious.

384
00:31:13.446 --> 00:31:16.949
- If you'll excuse me?
- I won't keep you any longer.


385
00:31:50.191 --> 00:31:51.192
Good afternoon.

386
00:31:54.695 --> 00:31:57.907
- There.
- Do you need any help?


387
00:31:59.658 --> 00:32:00.951
Yes, please.

388
00:32:01.327 --> 00:32:04.330
These things are all right in the water,
but very heavy on the bank.


389
00:32:06.749 --> 00:32:08.834
- Are you also a member?
- Not yet.


390
00:32:10.503 --> 00:32:12.797
- Have you been doing this long?
- A few weeks.


391
00:32:12.922 --> 00:32:14.924
I'm still getting used to it.
It makes my muscles ache.


392
00:32:15.007 --> 00:32:16.133
Why did you start diving?

393
00:32:16.425 --> 00:32:19.011
A friend recommended it.
Are you interested?


394
00:32:19.220 --> 00:32:20.221
Perhaps.

395
00:32:20.388 --> 00:32:21.931
- How did it go, Laura?
- Fine.


396
00:32:22.014 --> 00:32:25.810
Found your first suspect?
He's a policeman, be careful what you say.


397
00:32:26.644 --> 00:32:28.437
Did someone fail to pay
their parking ticket?


398
00:32:28.521 --> 00:32:30.398
He hasn't got any trouble parking.

399
00:32:30.523 --> 00:32:32.817
- Who?
- We're investigating a murder case.


400
00:32:33.150 --> 00:32:35.069
Oh, the heavy-duty stuff?

401
00:32:35.820 --> 00:32:38.197
Can I buy you a drink?

402
00:32:38.823 --> 00:32:40.282
If you don't mind waiting.

403
00:32:40.366 --> 00:32:42.118
I have to have
a shower and get changed.

404
00:32:42.243 --> 00:32:43.285
I'll wait.

405
00:32:43.536 --> 00:32:45.579
OK, see you in
the canteen in 15 minutes.

406
00:33:10.229 --> 00:33:13.357
I thought policemen
never drank while on duty.


407
00:33:13.441 --> 00:33:15.234
I've never been very dutiful.

408
00:33:15.443 --> 00:33:17.194
Have you made any headway?

409
00:33:17.278 --> 00:33:19.238
I've made some progress, yes.

410
00:33:20.030 --> 00:33:21.365
- Long time no see!
- All right?


411
00:33:21.490 --> 00:33:22.533
Martin!

412
00:33:26.203 --> 00:33:28.706
- How are you? It's been a while.
- I've been very busy.


413
00:33:28.789 --> 00:33:31.083
This is Mr. Visser
from the Amsterdam police.


414
00:33:31.167 --> 00:33:33.502
- Martin Ruysdael, pleased to meet you.
- Likewise.


415
00:33:33.586 --> 00:33:35.588
They're investigating those murders.

416
00:33:36.172 --> 00:33:39.425
I've read about them. 
Ghastly business.

417
00:33:39.550 --> 00:33:42.094
It's hard to believe such things
still happen in this day and age.


418
00:33:42.511 --> 00:33:45.264
- Fancy a drink?
- A bourbon, please.


419
00:33:47.641 --> 00:33:49.852
Any idea yet who this maniac could be?

420
00:33:49.935 --> 00:33:51.353
We're working on it.

421
00:33:51.437 --> 00:33:53.063
Are you also a member
of the diving society?


422
00:33:53.189 --> 00:33:54.982
I was for years, but not any more.

423
00:33:55.524 --> 00:33:57.193
I was even on the committee.

424
00:33:57.526 --> 00:33:59.945
But my practice got too busy.

425
00:34:00.029 --> 00:34:01.739
You're a doctor?

426
00:34:01.822 --> 00:34:02.948
Psychiatrist.

427
00:34:03.032 --> 00:34:04.783
- Here's to you, Martin.
- Thanks.


428
00:34:05.826 --> 00:34:07.411
I no longer had time for it.

429
00:34:07.703 --> 00:34:10.789
The last time I went scuba-diving
was about three years ago.


430
00:34:11.415 --> 00:34:13.959
- Have you ever done any diving?
- No, never.


431
00:34:14.043 --> 00:34:16.045
I recommend it.
It's very refreshing for the spirit.


432
00:34:16.837 --> 00:34:19.590
Especially in southern waters.
The coral reefs, the underwater fauna...


433
00:34:19.673 --> 00:34:22.134
It's a different world. 
Pristine beauty.

434
00:34:22.718 --> 00:34:23.928
I'll think about it.

435
00:34:27.932 --> 00:34:29.767
You're here!

436
00:34:30.142 --> 00:34:31.560
You've met?

437
00:34:31.852 --> 00:34:34.522
He must be the one
who got you into diving.


438
00:34:35.272 --> 00:34:36.899
You were talking about me?

439
00:34:37.274 --> 00:34:39.151
The police always want to know everything.

440
00:34:39.610 --> 00:34:41.403
But I didn't tell him a thing,
don't worry.


441
00:34:41.612 --> 00:34:43.656
I'm afraid we'll have to forgo that drink.

442
00:34:43.739 --> 00:34:46.242
- Are you two leaving?
- We're going to a concert tonight.


443
00:34:46.534 --> 00:34:47.952
Another time, perhaps?

444
00:34:47.993 --> 00:34:48.994
Who knows?

445
00:34:49.036 --> 00:34:50.037
Shall we, darling?

446
00:35:57.980 --> 00:35:59.148
Thank you.

447
00:37:01.543 --> 00:37:03.420
My, aren't we in a hurry!

448
00:37:03.504 --> 00:37:05.172
I'm sorry, I didn't see you.

449
00:37:05.297 --> 00:37:07.257
As long as the Lord sees us, right?

450
00:37:07.341 --> 00:37:08.425
Exactly.

451
00:37:10.969 --> 00:37:14.098
A pity. Such a lovely girl
joining a club like that.


452
00:38:01.979 --> 00:38:03.564
Joop, we're getting rich!

453
00:38:11.113 --> 00:38:12.322
CENTER

454
00:38:14.324 --> 00:38:15.534
Two flags?

455
00:38:15.659 --> 00:38:18.746
Red for where she disappeared,
and yellow for where she was found.


456
00:38:20.038 --> 00:38:22.666
Why did he drag her
so far down the canal?

457
00:38:22.791 --> 00:38:24.209
Maybe he wanted to teach her to swim?

458
00:38:24.960 --> 00:38:27.629
He likes to play with his victims,
so it seems.


459
00:38:27.713 --> 00:38:31.800
We know the victim, where it happened,
what time it happened, but nothing else.


460
00:38:31.884 --> 00:38:33.385
The local search yielded no results.

461
00:38:33.510 --> 00:38:35.846
- Nothing about the rope?
- They're still working on it.


462
00:38:35.971 --> 00:38:38.056
- The rubber from the suit?
- A regular wet suit.


463
00:38:38.307 --> 00:38:39.808
The broken tip of the knife?

464
00:38:39.933 --> 00:38:41.268
You can buy that knife anywhere.

465
00:38:41.393 --> 00:38:43.979
- Depth gauge?
- Nothing yet either.


466
00:38:45.355 --> 00:38:46.857
What about the patrol boats?

467
00:38:46.940 --> 00:38:49.902
We barely managed to get two.
Not enough manpower, it seems.


468
00:38:50.068 --> 00:38:52.780
It's something, but what's the use?

469
00:38:53.572 --> 00:38:56.158
Sooner or later he'll make a mistake.
He's not exactly careful.


470
00:38:56.283 --> 00:38:58.368
I don't want to wait and see.

471
00:39:00.037 --> 00:39:01.121
Visser.

472
00:39:08.921 --> 00:39:10.881
I'm not the only one who's dissatisfied.

473
00:39:15.219 --> 00:39:17.596
We can't let that
guy get away with this.

474
00:39:18.597 --> 00:39:20.474
We need some tangible results.

475
00:39:20.599 --> 00:39:23.101
Four victims in four days.

476
00:39:23.185 --> 00:39:25.145
People will wonder
what the heck we're doing.


477
00:39:25.229 --> 00:39:28.357
We're still investigating a few things,
but for now our hands are tied.


478
00:39:28.690 --> 00:39:30.192
Still no witnesses?

479
00:39:30.317 --> 00:39:32.236
No one, apart from the homeless woman.

480
00:39:32.736 --> 00:39:34.154
Maybe a few fish.

481
00:39:38.408 --> 00:39:40.911
I just got a
phone call from the mayor.

482
00:39:41.537 --> 00:39:45.499
He has some important visitors and asked
if it was still safe to take a boat trip.


483
00:39:45.582 --> 00:39:46.625
What did you advise him?

484
00:39:46.792 --> 00:39:48.919
That he shouldn't sit
too close to the edge.


485
00:39:52.172 --> 00:39:53.632
I know how you feel.

486
00:39:54.424 --> 00:39:56.051
The feeling of powerlessness.

487
00:39:57.344 --> 00:39:58.762
All you can do is wait

488
00:39:58.887 --> 00:40:01.682
for the critical tip, the crucial clue.

489
00:40:01.890 --> 00:40:05.561
But something needs to be done. We can
hardly declare the canals out-of-bounds.


490
00:40:05.727 --> 00:40:07.479
We might as well evacuate
all of Amsterdam.


491
00:40:07.563 --> 00:40:09.106
It's the safest option.

492
00:40:09.773 --> 00:40:12.150
Drastic, but safe.

493
00:40:15.237 --> 00:40:17.447
Why do you look so glum?

494
00:40:17.531 --> 00:40:19.283
- Is there a reason to be cheerful?
- Maybe.


495
00:40:19.366 --> 00:40:21.618
The lab has researched the depth gauge.

496
00:40:21.702 --> 00:40:24.329
It's almost certain it hasn't been
in the water more than three days.


497
00:40:24.413 --> 00:40:27.332
- So it has to be the killer's?
- We can assume as much.


498
00:40:27.624 --> 00:40:29.751
They also found a large salt deposit.

499
00:40:29.877 --> 00:40:31.545
What does that mean?

500
00:40:31.628 --> 00:40:35.090
We can rule out the divers
diving in fresh waters for now.


501
00:40:35.382 --> 00:40:37.968
We have to look for divers
who've spent a long time


502
00:40:38.051 --> 00:40:40.929
working on oil rigs,
or for a towage company.


503
00:40:41.013 --> 00:40:44.641
If we find out what kind of water
the depth gauge has been used in,


504
00:40:44.725 --> 00:40:46.310
we'd make considerable headway.

505
00:40:46.393 --> 00:40:48.687
Is it possible to determine
the kind of water?


506
00:40:48.770 --> 00:40:50.898
