He is gone.

756
01:00:22.318 --> 01:00:23.319
Taxi?

757
01:00:34.830 --> 01:00:37.374
Bastards!

758
01:00:38.000 --> 01:00:40.419
He's heading for Leliegracht.
Do we have assistance in the area?


759
01:00:40.669 --> 01:00:42.713
The cavalry confirms receipt.
We're on our way.


760
01:01:56.370 --> 01:01:58.789
BRIDGE OPEN

761
01:01:58.956 --> 01:02:00.082
Idiot!

762
01:02:18.142 --> 01:02:19.977
Are you coming,
or are you just gonna hang there?


763
01:02:28.569 --> 01:02:31.197
You can keep quiet for an hour,
or all night for all I care.


764
01:02:31.280 --> 01:02:33.782
But it's no use. 
You're not going home.

765
01:02:33.866 --> 01:02:35.951
- I've nothing to do with it, asshole.
- No?


766
01:02:36.035 --> 01:02:37.494
Enlighten me then.

767
01:02:38.245 --> 01:02:40.998
- Drop dead.
- Innocent people don't flee.


768
01:02:41.081 --> 01:02:42.416
Guilty conscience?

769
01:02:42.625 --> 01:02:45.002
Why did you do it? 
Was it revenge?

770
01:02:45.127 --> 01:02:47.588
Is that why you butchered
five innocent people?


771
01:02:49.006 --> 01:02:51.592
- I want a lawyer.
- Listen, asshole.


772
01:02:51.675 --> 01:02:53.761
I've had enough of your games.

773
01:02:53.844 --> 01:02:56.263
What do you think we're doing,
goat fucker?


774
01:03:06.857 --> 01:03:08.108
Your turn.

775
01:03:10.778 --> 01:03:11.904
Right...

776
01:03:13.113 --> 01:03:15.324
You don't want to talk, goat fucker?

777
01:03:21.830 --> 01:03:24.166
- Congratulations.
- Why?


778
01:03:24.250 --> 01:03:25.709
Don't be so modest.

779
01:03:25.793 --> 01:03:28.170
The mayor sends his congratulations.
He's very relieved.


780
01:03:28.295 --> 01:03:29.713
That seems a bit premature.

781
01:03:29.838 --> 01:03:31.382
Why? You caught him, didn't you?

782
01:03:31.674 --> 01:03:34.426
I thought the mayor should be the first
to hear the good news.


783
01:03:34.510 --> 01:03:37.680
We'll have to wait and see if it's
good news. He hasn't confessed yet.


784
01:03:37.763 --> 01:03:40.599
Don't worry. Everything points to him
as the perpetrator.


785
01:03:40.724 --> 01:03:43.811
Your problem is that
you're always such a pessimist.


786
01:04:47.791 --> 01:04:49.084
What are you doing here?

787
01:04:50.794 --> 01:04:52.129
Can I come in?

788
01:04:58.886 --> 01:05:01.096
- Do you know what time it is?
- Way too late.


789
01:05:01.430 --> 01:05:04.266
- Were you asleep?
- Like all sensible people.


790
01:05:05.559 --> 01:05:07.519
- Don't worry.
- I wanted to see you.


791
01:05:07.728 --> 01:05:08.812
Did you?

792
01:05:09.063 --> 01:05:10.814
I would send me
away if I were you.

793
01:05:11.648 --> 01:05:13.734
- Cigarette?
- No, thanks.


794
01:05:14.109 --> 01:05:15.361
Do you want a drink?

795
01:05:16.070 --> 01:05:17.071
No.

796
01:05:18.322 --> 01:05:20.991
- A sandwich, perhaps?
- Not hungry.


797
01:05:23.994 --> 01:05:27.081
You've arrested someone, haven't you?
I saw it on TV.


798
01:05:27.414 --> 01:05:28.749
That's right.

799
01:05:29.833 --> 01:05:31.293
You don't look too happy.

800
01:05:32.669 --> 01:05:34.088
I don't believe we've got our man.

801
01:05:34.546 --> 01:05:35.839
What are you going to do?

802
01:05:37.007 --> 01:05:38.258
I don't know.

803
01:05:39.134 --> 01:05:40.594
Wait and see.

804
01:05:41.553 --> 01:05:43.514
Are you sure there is nothing
I can do for you?


805
01:07:12.352 --> 01:07:14.480
What's this?

806
01:07:16.940 --> 01:07:19.109
Let's get the lamp out.

807
01:07:22.112 --> 01:07:24.072
Yes.

808
01:07:25.407 --> 01:07:27.826
Put it there.

809
01:07:30.120 --> 01:07:35.083
Such a hassle.

810
01:07:42.633 --> 01:07:44.968
Now what?

811
01:07:45.219 --> 01:07:49.640
What a fuss.

812
01:08:06.949 --> 01:08:08.492
What the heck?

813
01:09:10.095 --> 01:09:11.096
Jesus!

814
01:09:51.386 --> 01:09:53.889
Police? This is Brouwer.

815
01:09:53.972 --> 01:09:55.098
I just saw something weird.

816
01:10:18.830 --> 01:10:21.917
- Have you found Eric yet?
- I haven't a clue where he could be.


817
01:10:22.834 --> 01:10:26.505
- He didn't come home last night.
- have my suspicions.


818
01:10:27.589 --> 01:10:29.716
I don't like the
idea of you diving alone.

819
01:10:29.800 --> 01:10:31.843
You think there are more killers
swimming about?


820
01:10:31.968 --> 01:10:34.930
I already told you we're not sure
we have the right guy.


821
01:10:35.013 --> 01:10:36.890
Don't you worry about me.

822
01:10:38.558 --> 01:10:39.726
Is this the right spot?

823
01:10:39.810 --> 01:10:42.270
The boat should be here.
The grapnels are there.


824
01:10:42.312 --> 01:10:43.313
All right.

825
01:10:43.814 --> 01:10:45.524
Let's have a look then.

826
01:11:24.020 --> 01:11:25.689
How can you tell if something is wrong?

827
01:11:25.772 --> 01:11:26.982
We jerk at the rope.

828
01:11:27.107 --> 01:11:29.109
One jerk: everything is fine.

829
01:11:29.192 --> 01:11:31.069
Five jerks is an SOS.

830
01:12:02.058 --> 01:12:03.643
He's in the boat now.

831
01:12:03.769 --> 01:12:04.811
How do you know?

832
01:12:04.895 --> 01:12:06.646
- The bubbles.
- Which bubbles?


833
01:12:06.730 --> 01:12:09.649
The air bubbles have gone.
They're heaping together in the boat.


834
01:12:09.733 --> 01:12:11.234
Oh yes, of course.

835
01:12:34.216 --> 01:12:35.258
FEDERAL POLICE

836
01:12:35.342 --> 01:12:36.426
What's happening?

837
01:12:36.510 --> 01:12:37.594
I don't know.

838
01:12:40.180 --> 01:12:41.723
Everything is fine.

839
01:13:03.203 --> 01:13:04.162
Is that normal?

840
01:13:17.050 --> 01:13:18.218
Haul him up.

841
01:13:22.889 --> 01:13:24.474
He's stuck.

842
01:13:43.743 --> 01:13:44.828
Haul him up. Quick!

843
01:13:47.664 --> 01:13:50.208
- It's too late! He's gone.
- Pull him aboard, dammit!


844
01:13:54.296 --> 01:13:56.047
There he goes.

845
01:13:56.464 --> 01:13:58.717
The air bubbles over there. That's him!

846
01:13:59.217 --> 01:14:00.969
Chase those air bubbles. It's him.

847
01:14:15.150 --> 01:14:16.818
Hello, 302. Do you receive me?

848
01:14:42.344 --> 01:14:43.929
- We've got him.
- How do you mean?


849
01:14:44.012 --> 01:14:45.388
He's heading towards the lock.

850
01:14:48.058 --> 01:14:49.976
We have to close it from this side.

851
01:15:33.311 --> 01:15:35.772
Right, we've got him.

852
01:15:36.314 --> 01:15:37.774
Right under those bubbles.

853
01:16:12.767 --> 01:16:14.310
Where have you been?

854
01:16:14.644 --> 01:16:15.770
John?

855
01:16:16.646 --> 01:16:18.189
They've taken him away.

856
01:16:18.273 --> 01:16:19.733
We tried to reach you, but...

857
01:16:19.816 --> 01:16:22.652
- He shouldn't have gone diving alone.
- I couldn't stop him.


858
01:16:23.695 --> 01:16:24.946
It's not your fault.

859
01:16:29.617 --> 01:16:30.910
At least we caught him.

860
01:16:30.994 --> 01:16:32.120
Platoon, get ready!

861
01:16:32.203 --> 01:16:34.330
We've trapped him.

862
01:16:35.498 --> 01:16:37.292
Those air bubbles?

863
01:16:38.668 --> 01:16:40.545
I think he knows he's finished.

864
01:16:40.628 --> 01:16:43.840
He hasn't moved an inch.
He knows it's over.


865
01:16:43.923 --> 01:16:45.633
- He hasn't moved?
- No.


866
01:16:53.349 --> 01:16:54.684
Not long now!

867
01:16:55.226 --> 01:16:56.561
Aim!

868
01:17:08.698 --> 01:17:10.909
Dammit!

869
01:17:29.385 --> 01:17:32.013
I'm sorry. I should've known
he would never swim into the lock.


870
01:17:32.097 --> 01:17:33.890
He's smart. He makes us look like fools.

871
01:17:34.015 --> 01:17:36.392
Meanwhile he's had
plenty of time to escape.


872
01:17:36.684 --> 01:17:39.229
Hello, 504. This is HB. 
Do you receive me?

873
01:17:39.354 --> 01:17:40.730
Hello, HB. This is 504.

874
01:17:40.855 --> 01:17:44.734
Hi, Hans. Someone has broken into a shed
at the Amstel dock.


875
01:17:44.818 --> 01:17:47.028
It's probably the diver
you're looking for.


876
01:17:47.112 --> 01:17:48.238
We're on our way.

877
01:18:04.212 --> 01:18:05.672
- He's in that shed.
- What's he doing?


878
01:18:05.755 --> 01:18:07.423
No idea, but I
think he's still in there.

879
01:19:00.476 --> 01:19:01.519
- Everything OK?
- Yes.


880
01:19:01.603 --> 01:19:03.271
He must be hurt.

881
01:19:24.959 --> 01:19:27.503
- How do I start this thing?
- Press the red button, and give the gun.


882
01:19:36.930 --> 01:19:38.181
Goddammit!

883
01:19:51.986 --> 01:19:53.863
Row! One, two.

884
01:19:54.155 --> 01:19:56.616
Put the helm to port!

885
01:19:59.327 --> 01:20:00.536
Jerk!

886
01:20:59.929 --> 01:21:01.848
PASSAGE OBSTRUCTED

887
01:23:15.606 --> 01:23:17.108
There's the bastard!

888
01:23:17.942 --> 01:23:19.694
HB, this is 306. 
Do you receive me?

889
01:23:33.166 --> 01:23:34.167
Watch out!

890
01:23:39.881 --> 01:23:41.257
Shit! Fuck!

891
01:23:41.340 --> 01:23:43.676
Goddammit! Jerk!

892
01:27:37.201 --> 01:27:38.619
THE AMSTEL
YACHT-BASIN


893
01:29:03.287 --> 01:29:04.288
He's coming round.

894
01:29:07.708 --> 01:29:09.126
What are you doing here?

895
01:29:09.210 --> 01:29:10.628
I was in the area.

896
01:29:11.462 --> 01:29:13.839
How are you? Are you in pain?

897
01:29:14.757 --> 01:29:16.217
Did you catch him?

898
01:29:16.300 --> 01:29:19.428
When we finally found you,
he was long gone.


899
01:29:20.221 --> 01:29:21.722
What time is it?

900
01:29:21.806 --> 01:29:24.225
Where is Anneke?

901
01:29:24.308 --> 01:29:25.643
Staying with a school friend.

902
01:29:26.352 --> 01:29:29.522
Willy. What time is it?

903
01:29:29.855 --> 01:29:31.190
1 o'clock in the morning.

904
01:29:32.525 --> 01:29:34.151
Time flies when you're having fun.

905
01:29:35.778 --> 01:29:38.405
I shot him. Right in his diving goggles.

906
01:29:38.489 --> 01:29:42.409
We found some fragments.
We don't know if you actually hit him.


907
01:29:42.827 --> 01:29:45.579
I have to get cracking. 
No time to waste.

908
01:29:46.914 --> 01:29:50.042
You'll have to stay here for now.
It's not serious.


909
01:29:50.125 --> 01:29:52.169
The dart only grazed the bone.

910
01:29:52.545 --> 01:29:54.547
The doctor says
you need to rest a few days.


911
01:29:54.630 --> 01:29:55.923
Jesus!

912
01:29:57.049 --> 01:29:58.551
How are you, Mr. Visser?

913
01:29:58.843 --> 01:30:00.761
Excellent, thanks.

914
01:30:01.011 --> 01:30:03.764
You were lucky.
Everything is going to be OK.


915
01:30:04.056 --> 01:30:06.809
Those stitches can come
out in a few days.

916
01:30:06.892 --> 01:30:10.563
It looks like
you'll just have a small scar.


917
01:30:12.690 --> 01:30:14.733
You better go. 
The patient needs to rest.

918
01:30:14.859 --> 01:30:17.319
I wanted to discuss
a few things with him.

919
01:30:17.403 --> 01:30:19.613
That will be difficult.
I just gave him a sedative.


920
01:30:19.864 --> 01:30:22.283
He won't be able to talk
for the next 12 hours.


921
01:30:22.408 --> 01:30:24.451
All right. I'll come back tomorrow.

922
01:30:24.535 --> 01:30:26.495
- Can I give you a lift?
- Yes, please.


923
01:31:01.030 --> 01:31:03.657
It's you! Sir isn't here yet.

924
01:31:03.782 --> 01:31:05.117
I know. I'm a little early.

925
01:31:05.242 --> 01:31:08.162
Make yourself at home. I have to go.

926
01:31:08.245 --> 01:31:09.747
My mother's stomach is playing up.

927
01:31:09.830 --> 01:31:11.248
Nothing serious, I hope?

928
01:31:11.332 --> 01:31:12.666
Too many toffees.

929
01:31:12.750 --> 01:31:14.418
She always eats too many.

930
01:31:14.501 --> 01:31:17.338
I can tell her not to all I want,
but she won't listen.


931
01:31:17.463 --> 01:31:18.964
And now she's ill.

932
01:31:19.048 --> 01:31:21.508
- Wish her a speedy recovery for me.
- I will.


933
01:31:21.926 --> 01:31:24.428
Have a sherry while you wait.

934
01:31:24.553 --> 01:31:26.096
I had one, too.

935
01:33:57.039 --> 01:33:58.832
You're not playing games with me, are you?

936
01:34:06.882 --> 01:34:07.925
SALVATION ARMY

937
01:34:10.761 --> 01:34:13.013
Is this one of your new therapies?

938
01:35:15.492 --> 01:35:17.327
Hello, this is the Surgery Ward.

939
01:35:18.412 --> 01:35:20.038
Who would you like to speak to?

940
01:35:21.331 --> 01:35:22.708
Mr. Visser?

941
01:35:22.833 --> 01:35:24.585
It's very important.
I have to speak to him.


942
01:35:24.668 --> 01:35:26.503
OK, I will have a look.

943
01:35:45.439 --> 01:35:48.734
I'm sorry, but Mr. Visser is still asleep.
Can I pass on a message?


944
01:35:48.859 --> 01:35:50.694
Tell him Laura called.

945
01:35:50.903 --> 01:35:51.945
Yes, Laura.

946
01:36:02.331 --> 01:36:04.374
And tell him that the one
they're looking for...


947
01:36:04.458 --> 01:36:05.959
Just a moment. 
My pen is not working.

948
01:36:06.668 --> 01:36:08.253
Hurry up!

949
01:36:08.378 --> 01:36:11.006
It's really important.
You need to warn Eric.


950
01:36:11.089 --> 01:36:12.507
I know who it is.

951
01:36:23.518 --> 01:36:24.728
Hello, madam?

952
01:37:19.157 --> 01:37:22.369
- Hello, kids.
- We're here to see Eric Visser.


953
01:37:24.496 --> 01:37:26.081
Third floor.

954
01:37:26.164 --> 01:37:27.624
Room 316.

955
01:37:27.708 --> 01:37:29.418
I told you he'd still be here.

956
01:37:29.501 --> 01:37:30.711
But I saw it, honest.

957
01:37:30.794 --> 01:37:33.005
Just keep your mouth shut.

958
01:37:33.088 --> 01:37:34.798
I only want to warn him.

959
01:37:34.881 --> 01:37:37.634
How could he be
in danger in the hospital?

960
01:37:38.093 --> 01:37:39.594
Maybe he's not staying long.

961
01:37:39.678 --> 01:37:41.847
Four days, the doctor said.

962
01:37:41.930 --> 01:37:43.640
You'll find I'm right.

963
01:37:43.765 --> 01:37:45.058
I know these things.

964
01:37:45.183 --> 01:37:49.688
You'd better be careful
you don't fall in the water again.


965
01:37:51.815 --> 01:37:54.151
- From the guys.
- How kind of them.


966
01:37:54.234 --> 01:37:56.320
And a clean set of clothes.

967
01:37:56.528 --> 01:37:57.904
Any news?

968
01:37:58.113 --> 01:38:00.949
I'm afraid I have
nothing to cheer you up.

969
01:38:01.408 --> 01:38:03.994
Do you mind if I take an apple?
I'm starving.


970
01:38:04.077 --> 01:38:05.537
Be my guest.

971
01:38:07.622 --> 01:38:09.541
Someone phoned, asking for you.

972
01:38:09.624 --> 01:38:10.584
Who?

973
01:38:10.667 --> 01:38:12.502
A lady. Someone called Laura.

974
01:38:12.627 --> 01:38:13.587
What did she want?

975
01:38:13.670 --> 01:38:15.464
It was a bit odd. 
She hung up suddenly.

976
01:38:15.547 --> 01:38:16.631
She didn't say anything?

977
01:38:16.757 --> 01:38:19.092
It was rather vague.
She said something like...


978
01:38:19.176 --> 01:38:22.596
you were looking for someone,
and that she knew who. Then she hung up.


979
01:38:22.679 --> 01:38:24.723
- She sounded a bit incoherent.
- When did she call?


980
01:38:24.848 --> 01:38:26.058
About ten minutes ago.

981
01:38:26.141 --> 01:38:27.267
Why didn't you tell me?

982
01:38:27.351 --> 01:38:28.393
You were still asleep.

983
01:38:28.560 --> 01:38:30.645
- Where did she phone from?
- She didn't say.


984
01:38:32.064 --> 01:38:33.106
It's Wednesday, right?

985
01:38:33.190 --> 01:38:34.691
Yes, the 24th.

986
01:38:34.775 --> 01:38:36.318
What time is it?

987
01:38:36.401 --> 01:38:38.695
- About half past 5.
- Mr. Visser, what are you doing?


988
01:38:38.779 --> 01:38:40.447
What's the matter?

989
01:38:40.530 --> 01:38:41.698
Hurry, or we'll be late.

990
01:38:41.782 --> 01:38:43.950
- Late for what?
- Mr. Visser!


991
01:38:44.076 --> 01:38:46.244
- Hi, Dad!
- Daddy has to pop out.


992
01:38:46.328 --> 01:38:48.121
- Where are you going?
- I'll tell you later.


993
01:40:15.542 --> 01:40:18.211
- Can you finally tell me what's going on?
- Can't it go faster?


994
01:40:18.295 --> 01:40:20.213
This is a new car.
I'm still breaking it in.


995
01:40:20.839 --> 01:40:22.007
Are you crazy?

996
01:42:29.509 --> 01:42:32.012
It's OK. Everything is OK.

997
01:42:41.563 --> 01:42:43.064
I believe that won't be necessary.

998
01:42:46.651 --> 01:42:48.820
I thought it was you!

999
01:42:53.199 --> 01:42:56.036
Inform the station.
We could use some backup.


1000
01:43:00.624 --> 01:43:03.501
I believe you have some explaining to do.

1001
01:43:58.390 --> 01:44:01.142
We've been friends since our youth.
We used to do everything together.


1002
01:44:01.226 --> 01:44:03.561
We also started diving together.

1003
01:44:03.978 --> 01:44:07.732
He went on to make a living out of it,
working for a salvage company.


1004
01:44:07.857 --> 01:44:09.025
What happened?

1005
01:44:10.610 --> 01:44:11.903
Three years ago,

1006
01:44:11.986 --> 01:44:16.700
a ship in the North Sea lost several
containers with chemical agents.


1007
01:44:16.950 --> 01:44:20.161
He was one of the people to recover them.
They said it was harmless stuff.


1008
01:44:20.245 --> 01:44:21.579
What was in it?

1009
01:44:21.663 --> 01:44:23.998
Uranium hexafluoride.

1010
01:44:24.082 --> 01:44:25.709
But they forgot to mention it.

1011
01:44:25.792 --> 01:44:27.043
Who are "they"?

1012
01:44:27.127 --> 01:44:30.130
A state-owned enterprise
involving senior officials.


1013
01:44:30.755 --> 01:44:31.923
Did it go wrong?

1014
01:44:32.006 --> 01:44:34.551
They called it "an unfortunate accident."

1015
01:44:34.926 --> 01:44:38.263
One of the containers
had burst open under water.


1016
01:44:38.638 --> 01:44:41.725
I didn't recognize him any longer.
His face had been deformed.


1017
01:44:41.808 --> 01:44:44.811
The stuff was so radioactive
it messed with his brain.


1018
01:44:44.936 --> 01:44:47.188
He became increasingly erratic.
There was nothing I could do.


1019
01:45:48.666 --> 01:45:51.544
He withdrew from everyone.

1020
01:45:53.421 --> 01:45:56.674
The fun was over for me. I quit diving.
I couldn't do it any more.


1021
01:45:58.009 --> 01:46:00.303
I went to see him a few times.
I tried to help him.


1022
01:46:00.428 --> 01:46:02.847
A few months ago, he asked
if he could borrow my diving gear.


1023
01:46:02.931 --> 01:46:05.433
He'd got rid of his. 
Of course I said yes.

1024
01:46:05.725 --> 01:46:08.686
I wanted him to be happy.
I let him use all my stuff.


1025
01:46:09.354 --> 01:46:10.855
I had no idea what his intentions were.

1026
01:46:10.980 --> 01:46:12.816
Avenging himself against society.

1027
01:46:13.107 --> 01:46:15.193
Murdering innocent people.

1028
01:46:15.735 --> 01:46:18.780
I didn't want to believe it. He's sick.

1029
01:46:19.280 --> 01:46:20.323
Extremely sick.

1030
01:46:21.074 --> 01:46:22.200
We're nearly there.

1031
01:47:13.334 --> 01:47:15.086
He's in there. 
But don't hurry.

1032
01:47:15.211 --> 01:47:16.838
He won't ever go underground again.

1033
01:47:34.522 --> 01:47:36.024
Shouldn't we be getting back?

1034
01:47:36.107 --> 01:47:37.483
Your daughter might be worried.

1035
01:47:37.567 --> 01:47:39.152
She can take care of herself.

1036
01:47:39.277 --> 01:47:40.612
I've booked a table.

1037
01:47:41.487 --> 01:47:44.532
For three,
by candlelight at a fish restaurant.


1038
01:47:45.617 --> 01:47:48.077
- A fish restaurant?
- Don't you like fish?


1039
01:47:48.661 --> 01:47:49.662
No.

1040
01:47:50.079 --> 01:47:52.498
I don't like anything
that comes out of the water, to be honest.


1041
01:47:52.624 --> 01:47:54.459
I came out of the water, remember?

1042
01:47:54.584 --> 01:47:56.294
I'll make an exception for you.

1043
01:48:02.175 --> 01:48:03.593
You joker!